WHO EVER TAKES DOWN THE ORDERS OVER THE PHONE IS VERY NASTY, IMPATIENT, RUDE AND DOES NOT LISTEN TO WHAT THE CUSTOMER IS TRYING TO ORDER AND DECIDES TO GIVE YOU WHAT SHE FEELS SHE WANTS TO GIVE YOU. The place was a nice surprise we found while walking the area. It is slighty bigger than the impression  the corner facade gives. It was nice, bright, and clean. The pupusas and tamales were good, but the carne asada was better. The service was nice though the waitress was both kind and awkward; not the most courteous, but not the rudest. What puzzled me was that I payed the check planning on leaving her the change and 2 dollars more. I had no small bills so waited for the change to tip her. But she never gave me the change and just walked away ignoring me until I asked if everything was okay? She nodded and walked past me to the bar/ counter area. Well okay then... A nice meal turned awkward. Thank goodness the food was good.
